# Next.js + Docker Project Rules

When creating or modifying Next.js app code, Dockerfiles, Docker Compose, or related config in this project, follow these rules.

---

## Project context

- **Stack:** Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Vitest, ESLint.
- **Package manager:** npm (package-lock.json); Dockerfiles also support yarn and pnpm via lockfile detection.
- **Repo:** docker-nextjs-sample (Next.js + Docker sample).

---

## Next.js conventions

- Use the **App Router**: `app/` directory, `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, etc.
- Use **TypeScript** for app and config; keep types accurate and avoid `any` where possible.
- **Static export:** Use `output: "export"` in `next.config` only when building for `out/` (Dockerfile.serve, Dockerfile.nginx). Default in this repo is `output: "standalone"` for the main Dockerfile.
- **Standalone:** Copy only `.next/standalone`, `.next/static`, and `public/` into the runtime image; do not copy the full `.next/` directory.
- **Paths:** Use project-relative imports; avoid hardcoded absolute paths that assume a specific host layout.
- **Env:** Use `process.env` for runtime config; never commit secrets. Use `.env*` only for local/dev and ensure `.dockerignore` excludes them from build context.

---

## Docker: image version pinning

- **ALWAYS** pin exact base image versions. No `latest` or floating tags.
- Use ARGs for versions: e.g. `ARG NODE_VERSION=24.14.0-alpine`, `ARG NGINXINC_IMAGE_TAG=alpine3.22`.
- This project: Node `24.14.0-alpine` (serve/nginx) or `24.14.0-slim` (standalone/dev); Nginx `nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged` with Alpine tag.

---

## Docker: base image selection

- Use **Alpine** or **Slim** variants only.
- Prefer Alpine for static export (serve/nginx); use Slim when glibc or compatibility is needed (standalone/dev).

---

## Docker: multi-stage builds

- **ALWAYS** use multi-stage builds for production Dockerfiles.
- Typical stages: `dependencies` â†’ `builder` (or `build`) â†’ `runner` (or `final`).
- Name stages clearly: `dependencies`, `builder`, `runner`, `final`, `dev`.
- Copy only required artifacts: for standalone, copy `.next/standalone`, `.next/static`, `public/`; for static, copy `out/` only.

---

## Docker: non-root user

- **ALWAYS** run production containers as non-root.
- Use built-in users: `node`, `nginx` (nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged).
- Use `COPY --chown=node:node` (or appropriate user) and set `USER node` (or `nginx`) before `CMD`/`ENTRYPOINT`.

---

## Docker: layer caching

- Copy `package.json` and lockfiles before source code.
- Use `npm ci` (or yarn/pnpm equivalent with frozen lockfile) for production.
- Use BuildKit cache mounts: `--mount=type=cache,target=/root/.npm` for npm; optional `--mount=type=cache,target=/app/.next/cache` for Next.js build.
- Order instructions from least to most frequently changing.

---

## Docker: security

- Never hardcode secrets in Dockerfiles; use env vars or Docker secrets.
- Set `ENV NODE_ENV=production` in production stages.
- Prefer `nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged` over default nginx when using Nginx.
- Use explicit `COPY` of known files; avoid broad wildcards that could pull in secrets.

---

## Docker Compose

- Use unique, descriptive `container_name`s per service.
- Pin image versions in production; no `latest`.
- Add healthchecks for production services where useful.
- Use named networks and restart policies (`unless-stopped` for long-running).
- This project: `nextjs-prod-standalone` (3000), `nextjs-prod-static-nginx` / `nextjs-prod-static-serve` (8080), `nextjs-dev` (3000, watch), plus `nextjs-test` and `nextjs-lint` under profile `tools`.

---

## Package installation (Docker)

- Use `npm ci` for production; support yarn/pnpm via lockfile detection if present.
- Pin global or one-off tools: e.g. `serve@14.2.6` in Dockerfile.serve.
- Use `--omit=dev` or `--only=production` when installing only production deps in final stage (if applicable).

---

## File ownership and .dockerignore

- Set ownership on copy: `COPY --chown=user:group`.
- `.dockerignore` must exclude: `node_modules`, `.next`, `out`, `dist`, `build`, `.env*`, `.git`, IDE/CI files, Docker and compose files, docs, test/cache dirs. See project `.dockerignore` for the full list.

---

## Project Dockerfiles and ports

| Dockerfile       | Mode        | Port |
| ---------------- | ----------- | ---- |
| Dockerfile       | Standalone  | 3000 |
| Dockerfile.serve | Static      | 8080 |
| Dockerfile.nginx | Static      | 8080 |
| Dockerfile.dev   | Development | 3000 |

- Working directory: `/app`.
- When adding or changing Dockerfiles, keep the same multi-stage and non-root patterns; reference existing Dockerfiles and AGENTS.md.

---

## Code style (Dockerfiles)

- Use clear section comments (e.g. `# ============================================`).
- Keep ARGs at the top; group related instructions.
- Prefer comments that explain why, not only what.

---

## What to avoid

- âťŚ `latest` or floating base image tags
- âťŚ Running as root in production
- âťŚ Copying full `.next/` into runner (use standalone + static only for standalone mode)
- âťŚ `npm install` in production Dockerfiles (use `npm ci`)
- âťŚ Copying source before dependency manifests
- âťŚ Hardcoding secrets
- âťŚ Skipping multi-stage for production
- âťŚ Using `ADD` instead of `COPY`
- âťŚ Forgetting `NODE_ENV=production` in production images
- âťŚ Committing `.env*` with secrets or including them in build context

---

## Validation checklist

Before finalizing Docker or Next.js deploy changes:

- [ ] Base image version pinned
- [ ] Alpine or Slim variant used as appropriate
- [ ] Multi-stage build for production images
- [ ] Non-root user and correct `--chown`
- [ ] Dependency manifests before source; `npm ci` in production
- [ ] BuildKit cache mounts where applicable
- [ ] Correct Next.js artifacts (standalone vs `out/`) copied
- [ ] `.dockerignore` complete; no secrets in Dockerfile
- [ ] `NODE_ENV=production` and optionally `NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1` in production

---

